Living for adventure, love & spontaneity

social_posts.post_text:
Brought in the New Year with beautiful people in my favorite place✨🙏🏼💕 

I spent some time journaling on key things that I’ve learned this past year and wanted to share a few of them here:

• Getting the courage to find your true self is the biggest act of love, to yourself and those around you.

• Everyone is so beautifully unique, own your your uniqueness - it’s your biggest gift to the world because no one else is you.

• Life is distracting, consciously make time to connect to the present moment, to yourself and the people around you or it will pass you by. 

• Quiet that noisy mind and get in touch with your deepest desires and what makes your heart sing. Then set boundaries and learn to say no to the things that aren’t in alignment. People will love and respect you more. 

• You can be a kind person but also stand in your power. Ditch the people pleasing.

• You are never done “doing the work”, living a conscious life is “the work” 

• Learning how to communicate effectively is the ultimate life hack. If anyone has recs, please send them my way 🙃

More learning and growing in 2023 ✨

Fell hard for the pura vida vibes in Costa Rica 💕🌊✨ 

Santa Teresa has a similar lifestyle as Hawaii but there’s a Central American flare and rawness that makes it so unique and different. Surfed beautiful waves, ate delicious food, rode ATVs around town, and enjoyed every moment with the crew - what else could you ask for?

Special moments in 2022 ❤️

It’s not in our nature to grab our phone to capture the harder painful moments in life. 2022 was a lot of tears, crying, pain, uncertainty, hard conversations, deep work, & lots and lots of therapy. 

But there were also a lot of very beautiful moments; reunions, dance parties, deep conversations, best friends bachelorette’s and weddings, sunsets, spending time in nature, learning how to scuba dive, working hard, and traveling again…

Riding the wave that is LIFE 🌊🙏🏼✨

@trentalalala nailed it when she expressed in her vows… “I’m pretty sure everyone is jealous of me.” Yes, yes WE ARE!! 🤣

It was truly the most beautiful weekend celebrating the love between Woods & Rocky. Inspired is an understatement. I am still basking in all the love ❤️
It’s starting to feel like Spring on this magical little island ✨🌺🌊

30 ✨🕊️🤍

Celebrated my 30th lap around the sun a few weeks ago frolicking around Europe with the girls. So many emotions came up... peace, happiness, excitement, nostalgia, all very sentimental, and emotional. As I look back on my 20's I can't help but smile and tear up a little.

My 20's were spent with an open heart and mind, I can truly say that I've been living life to the fullest. I am so grateful for the deep connections and friendships I cultivated, the places I traveled, the unique love I experienced and shared, the new sports I learned, and the work opportunities l've had. It's all led me to the woman I am and the path that I am on now and I’m so proud of her. ✨

They were also some of the hardest years where I had to work through a lot to understand myself more deeply. I tripped on my face countless times and made A LOT of mistakes, but with them came a lot of realizations and deep understandings about why I am the way I am and in turn allowed me to have a lot more compassion and love for myself. I've learned that in any situation, if you take a moment to stop and reflect, there is a learning that you can take with you and implement to help your future self live with more integrity and in a stronger alignment with your inner truth.

Cheers to riding the wave of emotions, living with intention, and surrendering to whatever is meant to unfold. 🙌🏼

location.city_name: Black Rock City, Burning Man, Nevada

social_posts.post_text:
A few of my favorite )’( moments ❤️

This one was the most intense Burns yet - my intention was to surrender to every feeling and emotion that I needed to feel. Feeling that openness and truly surrendering to what was meant to unfold is exactly what I needed. 

My experience this year reaffirms the fact that BM gives you exactly what you need wherever you are in your life. It acts as a mirror, allowing you to reflect on yourself and see the bigger picture for what you want in this life. My experience was emotional, tumultuous, confusing, painful, challenging, and honestly, at times, really f*cking hard. I cried a lot, sat in so much pain, and I’m forever grateful for my girls @mallanee and @marlersinger for being my safe space to release these emotions and feel all the feels. But with all the pain also came SO much beauty, clarity, a very full and warm heart, a deeper connection with myself which lead to a the deepest level of intimacy that I’ve ever felt with those closest to me. Life is such a gift and “gratitude” is not a strong enough word to describe how I feel about being given this human mind, body, and soul to experience it all. Thank you, BM and BDE fam✨

Life has really been lifing lately 🙌🏼 

Filling up my soul with all the warm and happy places, people, & moments... In my era of living intentionally, loving, healing, and having fun along the way. This is it 🤍

Winter solstice reflections ✨ I can’t believe we are nearing the end of the year, where does the time go?? During the darkest time of the year, feel both the darkness and the light within you and know that one cannot exist without the other. Both give you strength and both serve a purpose. Go into the darkness - reflect, journal, re-evaluate, and then welcome the light, set new intentions on how you can continue down the path that is in alignment with your higher self. 

In a recent meditation, I prompted myself to visualize my higher self; the person I want to be, how I want to feel, what do I want to embody — who is she? This photo and this moment popped up in my mind along with visions… She walks this earth with bare feet and is grounded by Mother Nature. She gracefully stands tall like an oak tree with her roots helping her stay strong even in the craziest, most tumultuous storms. She swims in a sea of authenticity and is lit from within, she doesn’t need external validation. She is a vessel of love and light to flow through and when you meet her, you are reminded that you are these things too. 

There’s a lot that life throws at you and you never know what is coming your way— it challenges you and shows you where you still fall into old patterns. But with awareness, you can give yourself grace and giggle at the old pattern because this time, you aren’t going to let it take control or have the same outcome. Instead it’s just another piece of information, another beautiful lesson. And you can find peace knowing that you can always come back to yourself, and let the vision of your higher self illuminate and guide you. 🤍

This is life. This is living. This is healing. Pain, joy, love, grief, happiness, sadness, anxiety, peace… it can be everything all at once. Feeling vulnerable but also inspired to share because these are some of my most cherished, real, and raw moments from this past year. ✨💗 

2023, what a beautiful, chaotic mess. This past year broke me; I met the darkest parts of my soul and experienced the deepest heartbreak, but I have faith and trust that struggles are sometimes the best way for us to learn something that we need to understand for our life journey. 

All of the experiences over the past year have humbled me in the most transformative ways, allowing me to be more grateful and present to the beautiful, joyful moments in life while also giving me the strength in knowing that no matter what challenges you are faced with, you are resilient and strong enough to over come them. You will always be okay. 💗

Excited to continue to expand, evolve, learn, grow, adventure, play, love, build, and be present with all the emotions and experiences that make life so d*mn special 🙌🏼
